    "body": "## Problem\n\nAfter https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37730, if we produce lots of message in cmdline mode, then cursor become laggy if we quit cmdline mode. (This use nvim_parse_cmd to produce error, but should also reproducable with normal print)\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable({})\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"CmdlineChanged\" }, {\n\tcallback = function(ev)\n\t\tif ev.match ~= \":\" then\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\tend\n\t\tpcall(vim.api.nvim_parse_cmd, vim.fn.getcmdline(), {})\n\tend,\n})\nvim.defer_fn(function() vim.api.nvim_input(\":echo \") end, 10)\nfor i = 1, 200 do\n\tvim.defer_fn(function() vim.api.nvim_input(\")\") end, 10 + 10 * i)\nend\n-- then quit the cmdline mode, move the cursor, notice it become laggy.\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\nCursor move shouldn't be laggy.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2207 ge198037148` neovim/neovim@e198037148\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.18.7-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
